omgthatdress:
Shawl1885-1910The Metropolitan Museum of Art“The detail of the embroidery in the central genre scene of this shawl is highly unusual. Both the faces and the headdresses of the characters are extraordinarily detailed. The feather headdress is of a type found in Chinese opera, where an extended pair of pheasant feathers are used to indicate the character is a warrior figure–the height of the feathers signify the warrior’s rank. The pink crepe lining and two-tiered fringe are two additional details that make this shawl distinctive.”
